President Cyril Ramaphosa is assessing Mpumalanga's response to COVID-19 Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa assessed Mpumalanga's response to COVID-19. South Africa has seen its highest number of COVID-19 infections in a day. The country recorded 8,728 new infections. Total infections are now above 168,000. COVID-19: Rising numbers were expected - Ramaphosa A further 95 deaths have taken the death toll to 2,844. Gauteng has 49,937 cases and is rapidly catching up with the Western Cape's 65,841 infections. Over 1.7 million tests have been conducted. Recoveries are just under 82,000.